  <h3>Instructions</h3>

  <p>The document templating system uses "liquid templates."
  Generally, you can use HTML and variables surrounded in
  double curly braces like so: <pre>{{ job.file_number }}</pre></p>

  <h5>Job Object Reference</h5>
  <ul class="no-bullet code code-labels">
    <li>job.job_type</li>
    <li>job.file_number</li>
    <li>job.address</li>
    <li>job.city</li>
    <li>job.state.xxxx (see below)</li>
    <li>job.zipcode</li>
    <li>job.county.xxxxx</li>
    <li>job.old_owner</li>
    <li>job.new_owner</li>
    <li>job.client.xxxxx</li>
    <li>job.requestor.xxxx</li>
    <li>job.close_on</li>
    <li>job.underwriter_name</li>
    <li>job.short_sale</li>
    <li>job.file_type</li>
  </ul>

  <h5>Task Object Reference</h5>
  <ul class="no-bullet code code-labels">
    <li>task.job.xxxx</li>
    <li>task.workflow_state</li>
    <li>task.due_on</li>
    <li>task.deed_of_trust_number</li>
    <li>task.new_deed_of_trust_number</li>
    <li>task.developer</li>
